{{#if:|<p style="font-size:150%; text-align:center;" class="plainlinks">[{{filepath:Yttrium sublimed dendritic and 1cm3 cube.jpg}} View the animation]</p>}}
Three samples of '''[[yttrium]]''', a silvery [[rare earth element|rare earth]] metal. The left and the middle sample are [[Sublimation (phase transition)|sublimed]] [[Dendrite (crystal)|dendritic]] and the cube on the right was created by [[Gas tungsten arc welding|argon arc remelting]]. Yttrium is named after the town of [[Ytterby]], Sweden, where it was first discovered, and is used industrially in making [[phosphor]]s such as those in [[cathode ray tube]]s and [[Light-emitting diode|LED]]s.

